      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Muslim women with long shawls (called bošča) are walking in a Baščaršija street. A young boy in urban clothes and with a felt hat (fez) accompanies them. A man in traditional clothes 'à la turca' is standing in front of a shop which offers flatbread (lepinja or somun).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Lepinja / lepinje (triple-raised soft baked flatbread), also know as somun in some regions. On the back there is an advertisement for the so-called 'Bezweberei' ('Umjetničko-obrtnički zavod') which was established in Sarajevo in 1886 as an applied art center. Uncirculated postcard.</ab>
